article.headline: Brown 77, Hartford 65
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Jason Forte scored 24 points and Luke Ruscoe added 19 to lift Brown to its third straight victory, 77-65 over Hartford on Monday night. David Ruffian had 12 points to lead five double-figure scorers for Hartford (1-3). Freshman Mark McAndrew hit a 3-pointer with 11:55 remaining to give Brown (3-4) the lead for good at 45-43. That started a 9-0 run that ended with 7:35 left on a dunk by Ruscoe. The Bears were 25-of-40 from the free throw line, while the Hawks were just 2-for-5.
